HEADWORD: Mediant
<hw>Me"di*ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>medians</ets>, p. p. of <ets>mediare</ets> to halve: cf. It.
<ets>mediante</ets>, F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧diante</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>The third above the keynote; -- so called because
it divides the interval between the tonic and dominant into two
thirds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mediastinal</ent>⟦br⟧
